[~daijy] :: These hive tables are created on top of Hbase tables. Here is one of the sample commands we have used for creating it.

{quote}
CREATE EXTERNAL TABLE test_20150326

(MD5 STRING,

image BINARY

)

STORED BY 'org.apache.hadoop.hive.hbase.HBaseStorageHandler'

WITH SERDEPROPERTIES ("hbase.columns.mapping"= ":key#s,z:imagebyte#b")


TBLPROPERTIES("hbase.table.name"= "images_00",
"hbase.table.default.storage.type" = "binary");
{quote}
